  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 21 @ 2023/2024",
    "Question": {
      "content": "A uniform electric field of magnitude 2000 NC⁻¹ acts along the negative direction of y-axis. If an electron is projected into this field with a velocity V = 10⁵ ms⁻¹ perpendicular to the field. By how much has the electron been deflected after it has travelled 1cm in the x-direction?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "10⁻²m",
        "0.57cm",
        "9.11×10⁻¹⁹cm",
        "1.76cm"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "0.57cm"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>The force on the electron is\\( F = qE = (1.6\\times 10^{-19})\\times 2000 = 3.2\\times 10^{-16}\\,\\text{N}\\). The acceleration is\\( a =\\frac{F}{m} =\\frac{3.2\\times 10^{-16}}{9.11\\times 10^{-31}}\\approx 3.51\\times 10^{14}\\,\\text{m/s}^2\\). In the x-direction, velocity is constant at\\( 10^5\\,\\text{m/s}\\), so time to travel 1cm (0.01m) is\\( t =\\frac{0.01}{10^5} = 10^{-7}\\,\\text{s}\\). Deflection in y-direction is\\( y =\\frac{1}{2} a t^2 =\\frac{1}{2}\\times 3.51\\times 10^{14}\\times (10^{-7})^2\\approx 0.0057\\,\\text{m} = 0.57\\,\\text{cm}\\).</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
      "Electric Fields",
      "Coulomb's Law",
      "Motion of Charged Particles"
    ]
  }
